org.matsim.core.api.experimental.events

Interface EventsManager

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    EventsManagerImpl, ParallelEventsManager, ParallelEventsManagerImpl, SingleHandlerEventsManager

    public interface EventsManager
    This should be split into two interfaces: an API (add/removeHandler) and an SPI (Service Provider Interface)

      • resetHandlers

      • initProcessing

        void initProcessing()
        Called before the first event is sent for processing. Allows to initialize internal data structures used to process events.

      • afterSimStep

        void afterSimStep(double time)
        Called by a Steppable Mobsim after each doSimStep call. Parallel implementations of an EventsManager can then ensure that all events of the sim step have been processed.

      • finishProcessing

        void finishProcessing()
        Called after the last event is sent for processing. The method must only return when all events are completely processing (in case they are not directly processed in processEvent(Event)). Can be used to clean up internal data structures used to process events.
